WEBVTT

02:45.041 --> 02:46.997
All right, boys.

02:50.004 --> 02:51.540
Let's eat.

03:07.980 --> 03:09.720
Be there soon.

03:20.743 --> 03:22.859
I've been thinking.

03:22.995 --> 03:25.862
If you don't want to, you don't need
to go back to the oollegium.

03:25.998 --> 03:27.613
Antony's orders
don't stand now, do they?

03:27.750 --> 03:30.537
The orders haven't been rescinded.

03:30.669 --> 03:32.751
There's naught there
but thieves and out—throats.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.620
It's no life for children.

03:34.757 --> 03:35.997
Then where?

03:36.133 --> 03:38.419
Where can they find
respect and dignity now?

03:38.552 --> 03:41.385
Where can they live
without contempt?

03:42.014 --> 03:44.255
Take 'em anyplace but there.

03:44.392 --> 03:47.099
Go far away.
Who's to know?

03:47.228 --> 03:48.092
Lie, you mean?

03:48.229 --> 03:50.390
Live dishonestly?

03:53.567 --> 03:56.434
Well, there's lies
and there's lies, innit?

03:56.570 --> 03:59.607
This way.
That's it, come on.

04:00.324 --> 04:02.360
What's this, then?

04:05.579 --> 04:08.195
Put it right here.

04:11.585 --> 04:14.668
By whose authority
do you block the road?

04:14.797 --> 04:17.664
By authority
of Gaius Octavian Caesar.

04:17.800 --> 04:20.212
Go hold your horse.
We'll get to you.

04:23.347 --> 04:24.462
Sister!

04:34.650 --> 04:36.606
Not yet.

04:36.735 --> 04:39.226
We can't run off without any money.

04:43.617 --> 04:45.153
Octavian has brought
his army to Rome?

04:45.286 --> 04:49.074
Put up camp yesterday
on the field of Mars — 15,000 men.

04:55.463 --> 04:57.328
Your boy's a bit
aggressive, isn't he?

04:57.465 --> 05:00.172
My boy gave
your man a whipping.

05:00.301 --> 05:02.508
Expect he knows what he's doing.

05:08.934 --> 05:10.720
My dear boy.

05:12.146 --> 05:14.979
You are a hero of the Republic.

05:15.941 --> 05:19.900
Caesar himself could not
have conjured a finer victory.

05:20.029 --> 05:22.020
I am Caesar himself...

05:22.156 --> 05:23.316
technically speaking.

05:23.449 --> 05:25.690
lndeed.

05:25.826 --> 05:28.363
On behalf of the Senate,

05:28.496 --> 05:31.203
we are deeply thankful.

05:31.332 --> 05:34.199
Not quite thankful enough
to give me the triumph | asked for?

05:34.335 --> 05:36.826
Now there,
I'm doing you a favour.

05:36.962 --> 05:40.375
Mutina was a lovely victory,
it's true.

05:40.508 --> 05:42.624
But it was a victory over other Romans,

05:42.760 --> 05:44.546
and with all respect,

05:44.678 --> 05:46.088
Hirtius and Pansa...

05:46.222 --> 05:49.180
Hirtius and Pansa are dead.

05:51.268 --> 05:53.259
May the gods feed them honey.

05:54.230 --> 05:55.515
They are dead.

05:57.566 --> 06:00.433
But it is well known that
actual command of the battle

06:00.569 --> 06:01.979
was in their hands.

06:02.112 --> 06:04.603
The purpose of a battle
is to remain alive.

06:04.740 --> 06:06.901
They did not. I did.

06:07.034 --> 06:08.695
lndeed.

06:08.827 --> 06:12.570
Even so, the victory
is not quite complete.

06:13.874 --> 06:16.331
Mark Antony still lives.
He still has men.

06:16.460 --> 06:20.453
We have had to send
Marcus Lepidus and two legions north.

06:20.589 --> 06:23.251
Lepidus?
Sending your very best, then?

06:23.384 --> 06:26.876
l have every confidence
that Lepidus will succeed.

06:27.012 --> 06:29.424
Then he may have a triumph too
if he wants one.

06:30.432 --> 06:33.970
The people would not
look kindly on a triumph.

06:34.103 --> 06:36.469
Not with your army
at the walls of the city.

06:36.605 --> 06:38.766
A little unsavoury, perhaps.

06:38.899 --> 06:41.140
Now there, there he has a point.

06:42.653 --> 06:45.395
How good of you to say so.

06:49.535 --> 06:51.526
l bend to your wise counsel, then.

06:54.623 --> 06:57.865
- No triumph.
— We shall find some fitting way

06:58.002 --> 06:59.788
to celebrate your glory.

07:01.213 --> 07:06.003
Perhaps a temple to Caesar victorious.

07:06.135 --> 07:09.468
— That sounds rather fine, doesn't it?
- If I cannot have a triumph,

07:09.597 --> 07:12.430
l was rather thinking
of taking the Consul's chair.

07:13.559 --> 07:15.424
You wish to be consul?

07:16.437 --> 07:18.473
It's a vanity, I know.

07:18.606 --> 07:21.313
But I think I deserve it,
and it would please my men.

07:22.026 --> 07:23.482
You're 19.

07:23.611 --> 07:26.853
You're too young to be a senator,
leave alone consul.

07:26.989 --> 07:30.447
My dear boy,
you've been listening to bad advice.

07:30.576 --> 07:33.864
You have no experience.
You have no connections.

07:33.996 --> 07:35.452
He has an army.

07:41.962 --> 07:43.498
Well...

07:44.548 --> 07:46.539
l'll speak with the other senators.

07:47.259 --> 07:49.841
We'll see if it's possible.

07:49.970 --> 07:52.632
Though if you were to be consul...

07:54.600 --> 07:57.342
you must promise
to be guided by my counsel.

07:57.478 --> 07:59.810
It is an office of high complexity.

07:59.938 --> 08:02.680
And I am well aware
of my inexperience.

08:02.816 --> 08:05.558
I will not utter a word
without your advice, your...

08:05.694 --> 08:07.195
consent

08:09.156 --> 08:10.521
Well...

08:11.825 --> 08:14.567
perhaps something can be done.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.991
Bumptious young fool.

08:22.127 --> 08:24.209
The consul's chair indeed.

08:24.338 --> 08:25.748
Yes, but you will give it to him?

08:25.881 --> 08:28.167
Why not soothe his vanity?
He can do no harm.

08:28.300 --> 08:30.416
He will wear the purple
as he wears armour,

08:30.552 --> 08:33.510
like a child playing at grown—ups.

08:33.639 --> 08:35.630
Come, Tyro.

08:37.893 --> 08:39.224
I'm leaving now.

08:39.353 --> 08:41.844
Are you sure you won't come with me?

08:41.980 --> 08:43.265
Busy.

08:43.399 --> 08:45.310
Mother.

08:45.442 --> 08:46.773
He will come to me.

08:46.902 --> 08:50.315
Make the first gesture
and you will have the moral high ground.

08:50.447 --> 08:53.063
I gave birth to the ingrate.
He will come to me.

08:53.200 --> 08:56.784
— You're delusional. He's not coming.
- Thank you, daughter.

08:56.912 --> 09:01.406
I really appreciate these little chats
we have in between your drug binges.

09:02.918 --> 09:04.954
I'll be going, then.

09:07.548 --> 09:09.584
Should I give him your love?

09:11.343 --> 09:13.004
What should I tell him?

09:16.557 --> 09:21.017
Tell him that he's still got all our money
and we want it back.

09:21.895 --> 09:23.431
All right, the blue.

09:23.564 --> 09:25.350
Does it come in linen?

09:31.697 --> 09:33.688
Blow on it for luck.

09:56.096 --> 09:58.473
These are my daughters
redeemed from slavery.

09:58.599 --> 10:00.555
The eldest has been prostituted,

10:00.684 --> 10:03.141
the boy is my wife's child
by another man.

10:03.270 --> 10:05.852
You will treat them with respect

10:05.981 --> 10:07.721
and kindness.

10:11.487 --> 10:13.773
Or I will know the reason why.

10:28.921 --> 10:30.957
Gets a good breeze from the river.

10:33.300 --> 10:35.086
We'll have it swept...

10:36.970 --> 10:38.881
and painted.

10:40.098 --> 10:42.089
You like it?

10:42.643 --> 10:44.554
Yes, Father.

10:46.313 --> 10:49.180
We're all of us
starting again together.

10:49.316 --> 10:51.352
There will be...

10:51.485 --> 10:53.851
awkwardness at first, no doubt.

10:54.363 --> 10:58.276
But we're a family
and we'll be together.

10:59.827 --> 11:01.783
As it should be.

11:03.497 --> 11:05.488
We will not speak of the past.

11:09.294 --> 11:10.909
Yes, Father.

11:23.559 --> 11:27.017
Still eating like a horse, I see.
I don't know how you stay so skinny.

11:27.145 --> 11:28.976
How dare you?

11:29.106 --> 11:32.815
I'm not skinny.
l'm slender maybe.

11:33.485 --> 11:35.441
You're skinny.

11:35.571 --> 11:38.859
— I wonder how you don't blow away.
- My armour holds me down.

11:43.370 --> 11:45.361
Mother sends her love.

11:46.874 --> 11:49.160
— Does she?
— She does.

11:49.293 --> 11:50.954
She would have come with me, only...

11:51.086 --> 11:53.543
she has this silly idea
that you should come to her.

11:53.672 --> 11:56.584
— She'll grow old alone, then.
- I know how you feel,

11:56.717 --> 11:58.548
but really and truly,

11:58.677 --> 12:01.635
what would it hurt
to let her have her way?

12:01.763 --> 12:03.014
She is your mother.

12:03.140 --> 12:05.973
Octavia, you were there.
You know what kind of a mother she is.

12:06.101 --> 12:10.265
The gods know I have reason
to hate as much as you do.

12:10.397 --> 12:12.388
More maybe.

12:13.483 --> 12:15.565
But where does that lead you?

12:15.694 --> 12:17.605
Who can you love
if not your own mother?

12:17.738 --> 12:19.603
She put her lover to beating me.

12:19.740 --> 12:22.777
You credit her with too much power.

12:22.910 --> 12:25.743
Antony has a hold on her.

12:25.871 --> 12:27.953
She's scared and lonely without him.

12:28.081 --> 12:30.197
She made a mistake.

12:30.334 --> 12:33.201
I should have thought you at least
would be on my side.

12:34.254 --> 12:37.212
Brother, please!

12:37.591 --> 12:41.004
Don't be like that.
There are no sides.

12:41.136 --> 12:44.219
I love you. She loves you.

12:44.348 --> 12:46.760
You can't turn your back on family.

12:47.601 --> 12:50.343
She put her lover to beating me.

12:52.314 --> 12:54.430
Her sweat was on him.

12:55.275 --> 12:58.142
So they had made love. So?

12:58.278 --> 12:59.984
They are lovers.

13:00.113 --> 13:02.946
Don't be so damn pious.

13:03.075 --> 13:06.738
You'd just thrown the family
into ruinous debt.

13:06.870 --> 13:08.735
For this!

13:08.872 --> 13:10.988
So you can play at soldiers.

13:11.708 --> 13:13.084
l might've beat you myself!

13:13.210 --> 13:15.747
Clearly there's no point
in further discussion, then.

13:15.879 --> 13:19.292
Please, don't be angry.

13:21.176 --> 13:22.882
Come home.

13:27.849 --> 13:29.259
Come home.

13:29.851 --> 13:34.060
I don't intend to enter the city until
the Senate has ratified me as Consul.

13:34.189 --> 13:35.975
I shall then live at Caesar's villa.

13:36.108 --> 13:38.520
If Mother wishes to visit me there,
no one will stop her.

13:38.652 --> 13:40.392
Consul?

13:42.489 --> 13:44.025
Why would you invite such trouble?

13:47.202 --> 13:50.535
But in public you will speak of me
only with the utmost respect.

13:50.664 --> 13:51.653
Is that clear?

13:51.790 --> 13:54.327
I would never say
anything against you.

13:55.377 --> 13:56.833
You're my brother.

13:57.295 --> 13:59.160
Thank you for visiting, sister.

13:59.297 --> 14:01.834
We'll see each other again soon...

14:01.967 --> 14:03.832
when I'm less busy.

14:12.102 --> 14:14.684
What a stupid arse you've become!

14:23.739 --> 14:25.730
We've been hard—pressed since you left.

14:25.866 --> 14:28.152
Shields up, leathers braced.

14:28.285 --> 14:30.025
We've done well to hold our ground.

14:30.162 --> 14:31.902
I hope I've done right by you.

14:32.039 --> 14:34.121
You've done well, l have no doubt.

14:35.125 --> 14:37.912
- Thank you.
— We go on as before.

14:38.045 --> 14:39.785
Pullo's second, you're third.

14:41.089 --> 14:42.465
Third?

14:46.344 --> 14:48.255
Whatever you say, chief.

14:48.388 --> 14:50.720
But I was thinking I'd be second.

14:52.100 --> 14:55.433
Not now, woman! Can't you see
we're talking business?

14:59.483 --> 15:00.939
Anything else you'd like?

15:01.068 --> 15:02.899
See if the children want anything.

15:04.946 --> 15:06.106
Will do, boss.

15:09.326 --> 15:12.944
Being captain
all these long months,

15:13.080 --> 15:14.911
it's only justice, isn't it?

15:15.582 --> 15:19.245
If it's justice you're after, brother,
you're in the wrong place.

15:19.377 --> 15:21.538
Pullo is second. You are third.

15:22.422 --> 15:23.923
I die, Pullo dies,

15:24.049 --> 15:26.165
you move up.
That's how it works.

15:27.260 --> 15:29.046
I'll bet you 50 golden drachmae

15:29.179 --> 15:31.170
it's not me that goes first.

15:54.121 --> 15:55.452
Lucius Vorenus.

15:57.040 --> 16:00.032
Raise your head, Lyde.
I'm harmless enough.

16:07.467 --> 16:09.378
You're in a temple now?

16:10.470 --> 16:12.131
The altar of blessed Orbona.

16:12.722 --> 16:14.929
Good.

16:15.058 --> 16:17.640
— And you're well?
- I am.

16:20.230 --> 16:22.186
The children...

16:22.315 --> 16:23.896
are they all right?

16:26.444 --> 16:28.435
They're well enough.

16:34.911 --> 16:36.776
Listen.

16:37.455 --> 16:40.413
Don't think you can take them away.

16:40.542 --> 16:42.373
They're staying with me.

16:56.516 --> 16:58.381
Lyde!

16:58.518 --> 17:02.887
My loves! My loves!
My loves! My loves!

17:04.983 --> 17:07.645
Praise the great goddess,
you are returned.

17:10.572 --> 17:13.530
Blessed Orbona,
I will fulfil my vow.

17:23.710 --> 17:28.044
Praise her goodness.
Praise her goodness.

17:29.674 --> 17:31.710
Praise her goodness.

17:44.898 --> 17:47.731
Come to bed, love.

17:51.529 --> 17:54.111
What's wrong, princess?

17:54.241 --> 17:56.232
Why are you crying?

17:58.245 --> 17:59.360
Tell me.

17:59.913 --> 18:02.700
It's something I've done, I expect.

18:06.169 --> 18:09.832
Why do you leave me
with these bad people?

18:09.965 --> 18:12.627
They treated you all right, didn't they?

18:13.677 --> 18:16.089
Name the one
that didn't treat you right

18:16.221 --> 18:18.678
— and I'll see to it.
— It's not the point.

18:18.807 --> 18:21.469
Why do you leave me here
for Vorenus?

18:21.601 --> 18:23.512
He needed my help.

18:23.645 --> 18:26.557
I couldn't let it lie. The children.

18:28.817 --> 18:30.182
Vorenus...

18:30.318 --> 18:31.979
him you love.

18:32.112 --> 18:33.318
Me, no.

18:35.073 --> 18:36.108
No.

18:37.158 --> 18:39.240
You, yes.

18:41.621 --> 18:43.122
He more.

18:43.248 --> 18:44.738
No.

18:45.792 --> 18:48.283
No question.

18:48.420 --> 18:51.503
If both of you were
drowning in the river,

18:51.631 --> 18:54.498
l'd save you first.

18:54.634 --> 18:56.465
No question.

18:59.431 --> 19:00.887
Swear?

19:02.851 --> 19:05.012
I swear.

19:05.145 --> 19:07.511
You're half his weight.

19:07.647 --> 19:09.353
Half?

19:09.482 --> 19:11.473
Half his weight.

19:11.943 --> 19:14.685
Not so heavy. Easier to save.

19:14.821 --> 19:16.482
Never mind.

19:40.847 --> 19:42.553
Mother.

19:42.682 --> 19:44.297
It's so good to see you.

19:58.907 --> 20:00.738
My son.

20:01.618 --> 20:03.404
My son...

20:03.536 --> 20:05.697
forgive me.

20:08.041 --> 20:10.953
Forgive me.
I've been wicked and cruel.

20:11.086 --> 20:12.166
Beat me, kill me.

20:12.295 --> 20:14.581
Do what you want,
but just please...

20:14.714 --> 20:17.751
— please forgive me.
— Mother, please...

20:17.884 --> 20:21.217
I spit on that pig Antony
for leading me astray.

20:21.346 --> 20:24.429
I've been a terrible mother,
but I can change.

20:24.557 --> 20:27.219
And I will change
if you just give me a chance.

20:29.854 --> 20:32.186
My darling only son.

20:32.315 --> 20:34.476
Gods be my witness...

20:35.568 --> 20:37.729
I am so sorry.

20:39.489 --> 20:41.400
I'm so sorry.

20:48.832 --> 20:50.493
I forgive you.

20:52.919 --> 20:53.908
Thank you.

20:58.425 --> 21:00.882
Thank you.

21:14.816 --> 21:17.728
Look who's here, daughter.

21:17.861 --> 21:21.399
Our beloved Octavian
has blessed us with his forgiveness.

21:35.086 --> 21:36.997
Welcome home, brother.

21:48.016 --> 21:49.847
Father Janus,

21:49.976 --> 21:53.184
| ask you to cleanse these children

21:53.313 --> 21:56.055
of the dark spirits
that have fouled them.

22:30.683 --> 22:33.299
I thank you for bringing
my family back to me.

22:34.729 --> 22:38.472
I swear to you
that from this day

22:38.608 --> 22:39.893
l renounce darkness

22:40.026 --> 22:42.813
and I will walk in the path of light.

22:56.834 --> 22:58.870
Right, left, right!

23:11.474 --> 23:12.759
Lepidus...

23:17.730 --> 23:19.641
My old friend.

23:21.651 --> 23:23.516
How are you?

23:23.653 --> 23:25.234
I've seen better days.

23:26.030 --> 23:27.941
Off you go, boys.

23:28.074 --> 23:30.656
I don't think General Lepidus has any...

23:30.785 --> 23:33.447
ill designs on me.
Do you?

23:34.414 --> 23:36.655
Not under present circumstances.

23:39.127 --> 23:40.742
Come on.

23:42.046 --> 23:45.584
My men deserted to your side
with amazing alacrity.

23:46.759 --> 23:50.422
Not a single blow struck,
yet my camp is empty.

23:51.598 --> 23:52.883
Amazing.

23:53.016 --> 23:57.100
Yes, I really must write
to Cicero and the Senate.

23:57.228 --> 23:59.970
It was remarkably
generous of them to give me

24:00.106 --> 24:01.846
so many fresh troops.

24:01.983 --> 24:03.974
I confess I had no idea

24:04.110 --> 24:06.396
how popular you are
with the rank and file.

24:07.614 --> 24:11.357
Soldiers like a little spit and dirt
in their leaders.

24:11.993 --> 24:14.575
You were too noble
for them, perhaps.

24:14.704 --> 24:17.616
Too aristocratic.

24:20.126 --> 24:21.832
That may be so.

24:24.964 --> 24:26.500
So...

24:26.633 --> 24:29.249
what to do now?

24:30.303 --> 24:33.261
Strictly speaking, of course,

24:33.389 --> 24:35.641
I should kill you.

24:38.603 --> 24:41.561
I really don't wish to be punitive.

24:41.689 --> 24:44.021
But on the other hand,
I can't really let you go either.

24:44.150 --> 24:47.438
So...what to do?

24:47.570 --> 24:49.231
What to do?

24:53.993 --> 24:57.702
Would you be willing to act
as my second in command?

24:59.666 --> 25:01.327
Dear me.

25:05.505 --> 25:07.666
That's very generous of you.

25:11.636 --> 25:12.876
Yes or no?

25:13.513 --> 25:15.424
Well, |...

25:15.556 --> 25:19.048
I can't really say no, can I?

25:19.560 --> 25:22.848
No, you can't.

25:25.983 --> 25:28.565
I swear to you, four nipples.

25:29.612 --> 25:31.773
How is married life, Pullo?

25:31.906 --> 25:33.988
Well enough. Women, eh?

25:34.659 --> 25:38.026
It's a strange, awkward arrangement
to be thrust up and...

25:38.162 --> 25:40.027
bound against another so.

25:40.164 --> 25:42.075
But it seems to be the natural state
of man and woman.

25:42.208 --> 25:44.915
— It must be right and good.
- No doubt.

25:45.044 --> 25:46.750
Listen to me,

25:46.879 --> 25:48.835
a lamb lecturing a lion.

25:50.174 --> 25:52.085
Any plans to wed, then?

25:52.218 --> 25:54.459
I'm thinking about it.

25:55.972 --> 25:58.930
So Vorenus and his family
are back in Rome?

25:59.058 --> 26:00.559
Yes.

26:01.811 --> 26:03.347
My friend asks you to understand

26:03.479 --> 26:06.721
that he remains under loyal oath
to the man up north.

26:06.858 --> 26:09.224
But he will do what's best for the city.

26:10.695 --> 26:14.813
He acknowledges that you're
legal custodian of the Republic

26:14.949 --> 26:17.281
and will keep the peace
the same as before.

26:17.410 --> 26:19.492
Tell your friend I'm grateful,

26:19.620 --> 26:22.783
but I hear there is a deal of violence
again between the collegia.

26:22.915 --> 26:24.451
No trouble.

26:24.584 --> 26:27.121
We may need to bang
a few heads together.

26:27.253 --> 26:30.120
- Maybe.
— Whatever needs to be done.

26:30.256 --> 26:31.837
A period of calm is essential.

26:35.428 --> 26:40.422
